<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-12T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-12T10:00:00-05:00" n="402" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1120 H 87/11: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-12T12:00:00-03:00"><hi rend="italic">August 12,
                                        1922—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 4:14
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>89. Please instruct as to whether Mexican and Greek Special Ambassadors
                            and resident diplomats shall be invited to entertainments given by the
                            Secretary while here.<note n="24" xml:id="d402fn24">For papers relating
                                to the question of the recognition of the Mexican Government, see
                                    <ref target="frus1922v02#pg_639">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, pp. 639</ref> ff.; of the Greek Government, <ref target="frus1922v02#pg_409"><hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, pp.
                                    409</ref> ff.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>